PIN.values: |Random start position for Agents.&cr;&lf;&cr;&lf;Perlin's (3d) input Z coordinate is just shifting slowly (with the noiseZVelocity) from some random position.&cr;&lf;&cr;&lf;The output of Perlin Noise is roughly -0.35 to 0.35. MapRange (Value) is mapping this range to 0..1 which corresponds to the output of processings noise() function. &cr;&lf;&cr;&lf;Switches between noise modes.&cr;&lf;&cr;&lf;Angles in vvvv are between 0 and 1 so to comply to the Processing sample this has to be divided by 2PI.&cr;&lf;&cr;&lf;Reduce the stepsize given in pixels (in Processing) to a meaningful value for vvvv.&cr;&lf;&cr;&lf;Converts from polar to cartesian coordinates.&cr;&lf;&cr;&lf;MapRange (Value) is wrapping the agents coordinates when they exceed the borders. But now in the moment of wrapping both the current and the old coordinate (between which the line is drawn) need to be set to the new value. So FrameDifference (Animation) is used to find out if there has been a big jump and if so....&cr;&lf;&cr;&lf;...the wrapped value will be used as the new and the old coordinate.&cr;&lf;&cr;&lf;When reducing the agents count the framedelayed spread will carry more agents than the current spread. Two GetSpreads (Spreads) are used here to get exactly the current amount of agents out of the spread for the Lines From and To coordinates in order not to confuse the Line with spreads of differing spreadcounts. &cr;&lf;&cr;&lf;Count pins of these GetSpreads are set to 'Agent Count' multiplied by 3 as there are three coordinates for every agent.&cr;&lf;|
